# Week 2 – Diagnostic Analysis

## Objective
Diagnostic analysis of sales and profit to understand profitability patterns, impact of discounts, and efficiency by region and category.

## Dataset
Sample Superstore datasets (same as Week 1)

## Tools Used
Microsoft Excel

## Analysis Performed
- Pivot Table 1: Sales & Profit by Region → State)
- Pivot Table 2: Sales & Profit by Category → Sub-category
- Pivot Table 3: Profit Ratio by Region (Profit ÷ Sales)
- Pivot Table 4: Profit Ratio by Category (Profit ÷ Sales)
- Pivot Table 5: Sales, Profit, Profit Ratio by Discount Group
- Discount vs Profit scatter plot (from raw table)
- Calculated total loss, profit ratios, and highlighted negative profit orders

## Key Insights
- West region contributes the highest sales and profits ($725,457.82 USD and $108,418.45 USD), while Central region has the lowest profit ($39,706.36 USD).
- Technology category has the highest profit ratio; Furniture has the lowest (<5%).
- Copier sub-category achieves high profit despite low sales; Tables sub-category under Furniture causes the largest loss (-$17,725.48 USD).
- Higher discounts generally lead to losses, even when fewer items are sold.
- Discounts totaling $322,582.13 resulted in a loss of $156,131.29.

## Recommendations / Next Steps
- Focus on improving profitability in the Furniture category  
- Review discount strategy to avoid excessive losses  
- Explore region-specific strategies for low-profit regions 
